==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nesslerize
<hw>Ness"ler*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[From
<ets>Nessler</ets>, the chemist.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>To treat
or test, as a liquid, with a solution of mercuric iodide in potassium
iodide and potassium hydroxide, which is called <xex>Nessler's
solution</xex> or <xex>Nessler's test</xex>, and is used to detect the
presence of ammonia.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 972 --></p>

<p><ent>Nest</ent>⟦br⟧
